head(BOD)
##   Time demand
## 1    1    8.3
## 2    2   10.3
## 3    3   19.0
## 4    4   16.0
## 5    5   15.6
## 6    7   19.8
ggplot(data = BOD,
       mapping = aes(x=Time,
                     y=demand))+
  geom_point(size=3)+
  geom_line(color=6)

ggplot(BOD,aes(Time,demand))+
  geom_point(size=3)+
  geom_line(colour=4)

head(CO2)
##   Plant   Type  Treatment conc uptake
## 1   Qn1 Quebec nonchilled   95   16.0
## 2   Qn1 Quebec nonchilled  175   30.4
## 3   Qn1 Quebec nonchilled  250   34.8
## 4   Qn1 Quebec nonchilled  350   37.2
## 5   Qn1 Quebec nonchilled  500   35.3
## 6   Qn1 Quebec nonchilled  675   39.2
CO2 %>% # below use data CO2
  ggplot(aes(conc,uptake, 
             colour=Treatment))+
  geom_point(size=3,alpha=0.5)+ #plot graph
  geom_smooth(method = lm,se=FALSE)+ # regression lines with se unknown
  facet_wrap(~Type)+ #different Type in different graph
  labs(title = "Concentration of CO2", caption = "Concentration")+
  theme_light()
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

CO2 %>% 
  ggplot(aes(Treatment,uptake))+
  geom_boxplot()+
  geom_point(alpha=0.5,
             aes(size=conc,
                 colour=Plant))+
  labs(title = "Concentration")+
  coord_flip()+ #transpose
  theme_light()+
  facet_wrap(~Type)

head(mpg)
## # A tibble: 6  11
##   manufacturer model displ  year   cyl trans      drv     cty   hwy fl    class 
##   <chr>        <chr> <dbl> <int> <int> <chr>      <chr> <int> <int> <chr> <chr> 
## 1 audi         a4      1.8  1999     4 auto(l5)   f        18    29 p     compa
## 2 audi         a4      1.8  1999     4 manual(m5) f        21    29 p     compa
## 3 audi         a4      2    2008     4 manual(m6) f        20    31 p     compa
## 4 audi         a4      2    2008     4 auto(av)   f        21    30 p     compa
## 5 audi         a4      2.8  1999     6 auto(l5)   f        16    26 p     compa
## 6 audi         a4      2.8  1999     6 manual(m5) f        18    26 p     compa
mpg %>% 
  filter(cty<27) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(displ,cty))+
  geom_point(aes(size=trans,colour=drv),
             alpha=0.5)+
  geom_smooth(method = lm)+
  facet_wrap(~year,nrow = 1)+
  labs(x="Engine",
       y="MPG in the city",
       title = "Fuel efficiency")+
  theme(plot.title=element_text(hjust = 0.5))
## Warning: Using size for a discrete variable is not advised.
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'
